data.text:
Summer is the perfect moment to enjoy some seriously hot swimwear from the greatest swimsuit models of all time. Here are supermodels from the 1990s, legends from the 1980s, and the newest generation of bathing beauties according to Discover Walks. These surf and sand superstars sizzled in everything from exposing bikinis to unexpectedly sensual one-pieces, offering plenty of ideas for how to style swimwear along the way.

Informally, a “bikini model” is any woman who poses in a bikini for fashion magazines, advertisements, and photo shoots. The phrase can be used by both professional and amateur models. Swimsuit models, who are frequently featured in advertising and promotional materials, are not included. Bikini models must have a rigorous line of work.

Here are 35 Cutest Top Swimsuit Models

1. Hannah Stocking

Stocking who is an American internet personality, model, and actress was born in 1992. 19.8 million people follow her on Instagram, 7.72 million people follow her on YouTube, and 24.69 million people follow her on TikTok.

Hannah is a host of the YouTube music conversation show Mindie, which is created by Shots Studios. She has a typical body, a voluptuous face, and appealing blue eyes.

Hannah served as the face of the Billboard music magazine’s 2017 cover. Because of Hannah’s collaboration with Casey Neistat, another well-known social media influencer, The Neistat Brothers, a YouTube series, was created in October 2017.

2. Elsa Hosk

Hosk is a former victoria’s secret Angel. She was born in 1988. Ela Hosk is a Swedish model and has worked for Dior, Dolce& Gabbana, Ungaro, H&M, Anna Sui, Lily Pulitzer, and Guess. She posed for victoria’s Secret from 2011 to 2018 participating in the brand’s annual fashion show.

She has also appeared in a number of commercials for the business, mostly for the PINK division. In 2015, she was chosen as one of the ten brand-new Victoria’s Secret Angels. Elsa Hosk feels confident in her thin form despite the public regularly criticizing her for having a too-slim and lifeless appearance.

3. Malaika Arora Khan

Arora who was born in 1973 is an Indian actress, dancer, model, Vj, and Television personality. She appears in Hindi-language films. In 2012, Arora was selected to be the UNDP’s first Global Ambassador for Women and Child Development. One of Bollywood’s most stunning and proportionate diva stars is Malaika Arora.

In addition to presenting the ninth season of Comedy Stars and joining the Super Dancer 3 judging panel in 2017, she started judging India’s Got Talent in 2016. Malaika is among the most seductive bikini models. For companies like Manish Malhotra, Rohit Bal, and Narendra Kumar, she has walked the runway. Along with her clothing business, which eventually expanded, she now owns a lingerie line.

4. Kate Upton

Upton is an American model and actress who was born in 1992. Although her father served in the US Army, she was raised in the unincorporated suburb of Slidell. She studied at the University of Louisiana at Lafayette before talent management discovered her and convinced her to move to Los Angeles so she could pursue a modeling career. Although once being referred to as “overweight” by the media when compared to the typical criteria of a swimsuit model, she always had pride in her appearance.

She made her debut in the Sports Illustrated Swimsuit Issue in 2011 and modeled for the cover of the magazine in 2012, 2013, and 2017. Also, she was featured on the 100th-anniversary cover of Vanity Fair. She made her acting debut in “Grown Ups 2” in 2013 and then starred in “Baywatch,” a 2017 movie office hit.

5. Sonal Chauhan

She is an actress, singer, and model from India who primarily appears in Telugu and Hindi films. Sonal has excelled in beauty pageants and debuted as an actress in the film Jannat. She is currently working as a model. Chauahan is a petite model who has been in numerous award shows and other events. When the 7th International Festival of Photography was held in Singapore in 2008, she was recognized as Miss Photogenic.

Sonal Chauhan has a supermodel-perfect physique and entrancing eyes. She has been a model for approximately ten years and a working actress for the past few years. “Hai Apna Dil Toh Awara,” her first feature film appearance, was a commercial success in 2006. In 2008 she gained a solid reputation in this profession after working on the film Jannat. she represented India and won the Miss Photogenic title in Singapore’s 7th International Festival of Photography.

6. Natasha Oakley

Oakley has been an Australian Instagram Model who was born in Bronte, New South Wales, Australia in 1990. She rose to fame as a result of the A Bikini A Day blog she co-founded in 2012 with Devin Brugman, a friend and business partner. The retail brand “MONDAY Swimwear” was created in 2014 by Oakley and Brugman.

Oakley has appeared on the covers of numerous international publications, such as Women’s Health UK, Women’s Health Germany, Cosmopolitan Australia, Cosmopolitan Finland, and others. According to Elle magazine, which also noted that Oakley was listed on the Australian Financial Review’s 2021 Young Rich List, the worth of Oakley’s businesses was anticipated to be over $63 million in 2022.

7. Demi Rose

Rose is an English model and was born in 1995 in Birmingham, England. She has appeared in photos for a number of publications, such as “Playboy,” “FHM,” “Daily Star,” and others. Demi Rose won the Playmate of the Month honor from Playboy in September 2015. Rose is one of the world’s hottest bikini models.

She started a modeling career at the age of 18. Demi serves as a role model for curvy women because she is a size 8–10 model and an advocate for body positivity. She’s done runway shows for brands like Easy Spirit Intimates, H&M, Ultimo, Club Lingerie, and Wonderbra. In addition, she has served as “The Sun’s” spokesmodel.

8. Chanel Iman

Iman is an American model who was born in 1990. She is best known for her work as a Victoria’s Secret Angel. Chanel was declared as one of the top 30 models of the 2000s by Vogue Paris. And she appeared on the cover of publications such as Vogue, Italia, and Vogue Mexico. One of the most prominent and successful plus-size models in the business is Chanel, who wears a size 4/6.

Chanel has walked the runways for Victoria’s Secret and was selected to participate in the 2013 edition of “Sports Illustrated Swimsuit Issue,” where she debuted as one of the company’s first plus-size models. She continued to serve as a VS Angel for a second year in 2014. Nike and H&M are just two companies that Chanel has worked with.

9. Devin Brugman

Brugman who is a model and social media star was in 1990 in Oakland. Devin gained notoriety for her participation in cycle 11 of America’s Next Top Model when she placed sixth. Tyra Banks and she presented together on cycle 17 of America’s Next Top Model. She has become an inspiration for curvaceous women thanks to her social media presence.

Devin started participating in gymnastics competitions at the age of seven. Prior to deciding to concentrate on her education at age 14, she competed till that age. While modeling has always been Devin’s passion, she first intended to pursue a career in veterinary medicine. She pursued modeling first time after competing at the 2010 IMG Models supermodels of the World competition

10. Amrita Arora

Arora who was born in 1978 works as a model, TV host, VJ, and actor in Indian movies. Malaika Arora, a host, and actress from Bollywood is her sister. Bombay was Amrita’s birthplace. She received her diploma from Life University in India. Amrita launched her modeling career by participating in Lakme Fashion Week India. Afterward, she worked as a photo model for a variety of companies, including Godrej, the State Bank of India, and many more.

11. Lais Ribeiro

Ribeiro who is a Brazilian model best known for her work as Victoria’s Secret Angel. She was in 1989 in Brazil and is of Portuguese and chantilly descent. When Ribeiro was a youngster, an Elite Models scout discovered her on a beach and she soon started modeling. After concluding her brief relationship with Elite Models, Ribeiro signed a modeling contract with IMG Models France in 2009.

Being the first representative from Brazil, Ribeiro joined the Victoria’s Secret Angel Agency in 2011. Lais Ribeiro stands apart from the majority of half-dressed women you will typically encounter when searching for bikini models. She is active with her many charity initiatives when she is not working with Victoria’s Secret.

12. Nina Agdal

Agdal was discovered on a roadway in her neighborhood. She didn’t have any prior modeling experience, yet she nevertheless entered the Elite Model Look competition. Although she did not win, she still signed a contract with Elite Models Denmark and finished school till she was 18. After graduating, she moved to the US, where her modeling career quickly gained momentum.

13. Kelly Brook

She is an English media personality, model, and actor. Kelly Brook has a number of well-known credits, including Piranha 3D, The Big Bounce, Confessions of a Shopaholic, and The Lookout. She’s also well known for her role in the TV show Smallville. Her Strictly Come Dancing competition in 2013 was another one.

When Brook was young, she started modeling and won a competition. As a result, she landed her first bikini modeling gig when she was 16 years old. She joined Elite Model Management when she was 18 and soon after started working for prestigious fashion brands like Chanel, Christian Dior, and Guy Laroche. She has additionally performed contract work for businesses like Pirelli and Victoria’s Secret.

14. Sara Sampaio

Sampaio who was born in 1991 in Lisbon, Portugal, came into the modeling World when she was 15 years. She has worked with Victoria’s Secret since 2010 after modeling for companies like Lacoste and D&G. Sara Sampaio has walked in fashion shows for Diesel Jeans and Zara in addition to being featured in various advertisements for companies like Victoria’s Secret and Lacoste.

Sampaio became the first Portuguese model to appear in Sports Illustrated and serve as a Victoria’s Secret Angel. She is the Giorgio Armani ambassador, a spokesperson for Missoni, and a model for Calvin Klein’s lingerie campaign. Sara typically has a scorching hot figure, a strikingly stunning face with thick eyebrows, and mesmerizing blue eyes.

15. Paris Hilton

She is a well-known American media figure, businesswoman, socialite, model, and performer. Her great-grandfather Conrad Hilton, who founded Hilton Hotels, is related to her. Hilton first caught the attention of tabloids in the late 1990s when she made a name for herself in New York City’s social scene and, at the age of 19, started modeling for Donald Trump’s agency Trump Model Management.

After David LaChapelle photographed Hilton and her sister Nicky for the September 2000 issue of Vanity Fair, Hilton was labeled “New York’s leading It Girl” in 2001. She rose to popularity thanks to the reality TV show The Simple Life, in which she co-starred with her friend Nicole Richie, and a leaked sex tape from 2001 with her ex-boyfriend Rick Salomon, eventually made public as 1 Night in Paris.

16. Sunny Leone

Karenjit Kaur has been known by her stage name Sunny Leone is a Canadian-American-Indian model and actress in the American and Indian film industries.

She appeared in more than 4,000 pornographic films in 2004 and was named Penthouse Pet of the Year. She entered a search for a new Playmate competition run by Penthouse Magazine. She was listed among the top 10 Bollywood actors in 2013 by The Times of India.

The Rock ‘n’ Roll Los Angeles Half-Marathon, which benefited the American Cancer Society, was one of the advocacy events she took part in outside of the acting industry. She also appeared in a PETA campaign holding a rescued puppy and urging pet owners to neuter and spay their cats and dogs.

17. Sommer Ray

She is a former Vine sensation, fitness model, and YouTube vlogger from Denver, Colorado who was born in 1996. Ray is presently a resident of Los Angeles, California, in the United States. She has amassed over 18 million Instagram followers because of her stunning images and workout videos. Sommer Ray is known for having a lovely face and alluring eyes. She also has a stunning hourglass figure.

18. Amber Rose

Rose who was born in 1983 is an American actress and model. When she appeared in Young Jeezy and Kanye West’s music video for “Put On,” she first gained widespread attention. Rose starred in Louis Vuitton advertising for the duration of West and Rose’s two-year public relationship, which began in 2008. Amber has a rather massive bust, which had a significant impact on her subsequent life. Furthermore, she has a toned figure.

A modeling contract with Ford Models was later signed by her in 2009. After making numerous appearances as a video vixen in hip-hop music videos, she would go on to gain further notoriety.

19. Gisele Bundchen

She is a model, activist, and businesswoman from Brazil. In the entertainment industry, Bündchen was the 16th richest woman in 2007. She was the highest-paid model in 2012 according to Forbes. In 2014, she was recognized as the 89th most powerful woman in the world by Forbes.

Bündchen was nominated for Favorite Movie Female Breakout Star and Choice Movie Villain at the 2005 Teen Choice Awards for her supporting role in Taxi. She has worked as a goodwill ambassador for the United Nations Environment Programme since 2009. At the age of forty, Gisele Bundchen still has a toned, seductive body and long, straight legs that have become her signature.

20. Alessandra Ambrosio

Ambrosio is a Brazillian-American Model, actress, fashion designer, entrepreneur and television personality who was born in 1981. Her work with Victoria’s Secret where she was the company’s first PINK spokesmodel has earned her widespread recognition.

Ambrosio served as a Victoria’s Secret Angel from 2004 to 2017, in addition to modeling for companies like Christian Dior, Armani, Ralph Lauren, and Next. She was ranked fifth on Forbes’ list of the highest-paid models, earning an estimated $6.6 million annually. The mainstream media routinely cites her as one of the sexiest women in the world. She is still quite lovely in a swimsuit on the beach with her daughter even though she is past 40.

21. Caroline Daur

She is a model and fashion blogger from Germany. She became well-known after she had over 700,000 followers. Thus, she is solely known as “Caro.” In 2014, she launched CaroDaur.com and began fashion blogging.

Since she started her blog, she has developed a reputation as a prominent global fashion influencer. With her blog, she has worked with companies including Valentino, Fendi, Dolce & Gabbana, and Adidas. She also collaborated to global campaigns for MAC Cosmetics, APM, and Dolce & Gabbana.

22. Barbara Palvin

In 2016, she appeared for the first time in the Sports Illustrated Swimsuit Issue. She joined the Victoria’s Secret Angels in 2019. She also works as a spokesperson for Armani Beauty.

A scout for models spotted her when she was 13 years old while out and about in Budapest with her mother. After filming her first editorial in 2006 for Spur Magazine, she moved to Asia and progressively booked jobs there. Palvin developed her acting career after portraying the legendary queen Antimache in the 2014 film Hercules. On the 2016 Maxim Hot 100, she was ranked number four. She has the appropriate height and body type, and people always adore her curves in swimwear.

23. Sophia Miacova

Houston, Texas, in the United States, is the place of Sophia Miacova’s birth. She is a well-known social media influencer and model in the United States. She enjoys popularity on Instagram with 2.8 million followers. Sophia has a seductive 36D-27-36 physique.

Miacova started working in the modeling industry at the age of 18. She participated in the 2011 Ford Supermodel of the World pageant, where she placed as the first runner-up. Sophia was featured in the 2013 Sports Illustrated Swimsuit Issue in addition to other prestigious publications like Vibe Italia. She has worked with a variety of well-known firms, including Guess, Triumph, and Forever 21.

24. Shea Marie

Shea Marie was born in California, US in O987. She wears a size 22–24. Marie started an internship with a stylist and bartended to pay the bills after graduating from the University of California, San Diego with a degree in communications and journalism. She then started Peace Love Shea as a passion endeavor.

Shea Marie is well recognized for being the first plus-size model to appear on the cover of the Sports Illustrated Swimsuit Issue and to have graced the cover of ESPN’s Body Issue in February 2014. She is employed by IMG Models, IMG Model Management, IMG Models Paris, Charlie’s Models, Charlie’s Angels Agency, and Images Model Management.

25. Camille Kostek

Kostek is an American actress, model, and host of television. A modeling scout came across Kostek while she was roaming the streets of Manhattan when she was 18 years old, and she then started modeling. Her appearances in commercials for Ralph Lauren, Target, and Macy’s have since occurred. She started presenting Wipeout, a TBS reality competition series, in 2021. She began working with GQ in February 2015 as an international escort for their swimsuit issue.

I Feel Pretty, a 2018 comedy from STX Pictures starring Amy Schumer, marked Kostek’s acting debut. After that followed the science fiction film Free Man, starring Ryan Reynolds and produced by 20th Century Studios.

26. Chrissy Teigen

Brooklyn Decker, a friend, and fellow SI Swimsuit model suggested Chrissy Teigen for the magazine. She shared the 2014 cover with Lily Aldridge and Nina Agdal after winning Rookie of the Year in 2010. Chrissy is one of the most well-liked Twitter users to follow because of her quick wit and sense of humor. Cravings, a cookbook she released in 2016, quickly rose to the top of the New York Times bestseller list. Luna and Miles are the couple’s two children, and she is married to musician John Legend.

27. Jessica Pereza

In 2011, the model was located through a search campaign for SI Swimsuit models.

Jessica Perez is a successful businesswoman in addition to being a two-time SI Swimsuit model. In order to assist models and independent contractors in managing their finances and bills, Perez released her Tycoon app in 2015.

In 2011, Perez took part in a program to find an eight-candidate SI Swimsuit model, and she was chosen as the winner. In 2012, she made a comeback to the subject as a rookie, working in Panama with photographer Bjorn Iooss. She went to Chile for a photo shoot next year.

28. Serena Williams

The most talented athlete has been Serena Williams. Both on and off the tennis court, the 23-time Grand Slam singles champion serves as an example. She is the founder of Serena Ventures, the mother of 5-year-old Alexis, the writer of the children’s book The Adventures of Qai Qai, and a true living legend.

In 2003 and 2004, Williams first appeared in the SI Swimsuit Issue. Afterward, Emmanuelle Hauguel captured her in Turks & Caicos for a picture shoot for the magazine’s 2017 issue. She had previously posed for advertisements and participated in brand endorsements, but modeling in a bikini was an entirely new experience.

29. Emily Ratajkowski

She is a model and actress from the United States who was born in London, England on June 7, 1991. The 2012 edition of treatsMarch!, a pornographic magazine, had her on the cover making her modeling debut. She subsequently had two appearances in music videos for the songs “Love Someone” by Maroon 5 and “Blurred Lines” by Robin Thicke.

Ratajkowski often distinguishes out thanks to her ethereal beauty. She appeared in the 2014 and 2015 Sports Illustrated swimsuit issues, and at New York Fashion Week in 2015, she made her professional runway debut for Marc Jacobs. Since then, she has walked the runways of Versace, Bottega Veneta, and Miu Miu during Milan Fashion Week as well as Miu Miu during Paris Fashion Week

30. Irina Shayk

Irina Shayk, a Russian model better known by her stage name, shot to international fame in 2011 when she became the first Russian model to appear on the cover of Sports Illustrated’s swimsuit issue. Models.com lists her as an “Industry Icon.” Irina Shayk’s extraordinary height sets her apart from other models. Irina exercises frequently to maintain a healthy weight-to-height ratio.

Shayk has made appearances in the American, Italian, Spanish, German, Russian, French, Allure, and W Magazines. She also has the honor of being the face of the upcoming Givenchy fragrance, Capture Woman. In 2013, Glamour France named her “Model of the Year.”

31. Megan Fox

Fox is an American model and actress. In the live-action 2009 film “Transformers: Revenge of the Fallen,” she played the lead role of Mikaela Banes, which is her most well-known role. In the upcoming film “Solitary Man,” she will play the lead part in addition to having a supporting role in Jennifer’s Body. With a flawless and alluring form, she is regarded as a supermodel. She has maintained her current physical condition through food and exercise.

In January 2014, Richie Loop’s song “Reality” featured vocals from Fox as a guest. On the annual AskMen list of the 100 Most Desirable Women, Fox came in second place after singer Miley Cyrus in April 2014. The 2015 Maxim Hot 100 Women list placed Fox at the top.

32. Heidi Klum

She is an American and German model who also works as a television personality, producer, and businesswoman. She was the first model from Germany to be chosen as a Victoria’s Secret Angel and she was featured on the cover of the 1998 Sports Illustrated Swimsuit Issue. In 2009, she became a citizen by naturalization.

In March 2013, Forbes ranked Klum as the highest-paid model in the world, with earnings of about $7 million between May 2012 and May 2013. Only after the wife of Tom Kaulitz was she ranked second among TV celebrities in terms of pay by “Forbes.” On Forbes’ 2017 list of the 100 Most Powerful Women, she was listed at position 45. In addition to having a typical figure, she distinguishes out for her “European” attractiveness.

33. Ashley Graham

Graham is a plus-size model and television host from the United States. Graham began modeling when he was twelve. She signed with Wilhelmina Models in 2001 after attending a modeling conference. Following a career in modeling, Graham earned her Sports Illustrated Swimsuit Issue cover debut in 2016.

When her debut book, A New Model: What Confidence, Beauty, and Power Really Look Like, was released a year later, it further solidified her support for the body positivity and inclusivity movements. As a member of the Themba Foundation, Graham has also taken part in missionary work in South Africa.

34. Rose Bertram

Bertram is a model from Belgium. She developed an early interest in fashion and began modeling at the age of 18. Her attractive features, including her lovely face and green eyes, as well as her proportionate physique, are obvious. Prior to working for modeling agencies in Amsterdam, Paris, and Milan, Rose began her career with Wilhelmina Models Kortrijk, Belgium.

When she stumbled with another model, Sarah Zavalloni, who worked there, she then decided to start working part-time as a waitress. In addition to working on Victoria’s Secret’s “The Pink Brand” campaign, Rose recently finished a campaign for Acne Studios. Rose is an ambassador for H&M. On May 2, 2012, Rose made history by becoming the first black model to grace the cover of Glamour Germany. She is currently a client of Models 1 Agency in London as well as Elite Model Management in New York City.

35. Gabby Epstein

Model from Australia, she is. She was included in the Sports Illustrated Swimsuit Issue from 2016. Other magazines, including Zoo Weekly, FHM Australia, Ralph, and Maxim Australia, have featured her as well.

She began modeling for a number of well-known firms after signing with Chadwicks Model Management in 2011 and Priscillas Model Management in 2012. Gabrielle is the face of the Australian Maxim Magazine. She has received the honor of being named the “2014 Sports Illustrated Swimwear Rookie Of The Year.” She frequently wears seductive attire due to her average figure and attractive looks.
